HEADWORD: Cellarer
<hw>Cel"lar*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>cellararius</ets>, equiv. to L. <ets>cellarius</ets> steward: cf.
F. <ets>cell⟦eacute⟧rier</ets>. See <er>Cellar</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A steward or butler of a monastery or chapter;
one who has charge of procuring and keeping the provisions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

